What is it?
Normally, when you press Enter, your full, multi-line prompt (with the directory, git branch, Nix shell status, etc.) stays in your terminal history forever. It clutters your scrollback.

Transient Prompt logic says:

While you are typing, show the full, beautiful Starship prompt.

The moment you hit Enter, replace that bulky prompt with a tiny, minimalist symbol (like ❯) for the history.

It keeps your terminal looking like a clean log of commands rather than a wall of metadata.

Option 1: The "Fish" Way (Easiest & Most Robust)
Fish has a native function called fish_prompt that makes this relatively trivial. Since you use Starship, you just need to tell Fish how to "clear" the prompt on execution.

Create/Edit: ~/.config/fish/config.fish

Add this logic (Starship has a built-in transient feature for Fish):

Code snippet
# ~/.config/fish/config.fish

# Initialize Starship
starship init fish | source

# Enable Transience
function enable_transient
    function starship_transient_prompt_func
      starship module character
    end
    type -q enable_transient_keybinds && enable_transient_keybinds
end

enable_transient
Result: When you hit Enter, everything disappears except the ❯.

Why it's robust: Fish handles the redraw natively. No weird flickering in Ghostty.

Option 2: The "Zsh" Way (The "Power User" Manual Way)
Zsh doesn't do this natively. You have to use a "leaking" logic where you capture the accept-line widget.

Because you want to learn "what's really going on," here is the manual breakdown. You need a plugin called zsh-snap or a manual snippet to handle the redraw. However, the most robust way is using the Transient Prompt feature in the pure or typewriter style logic.

If you are using Starship with Zsh:

Add this to your ~/.zshrc:

Bash
# Initialize Starship
eval "$(starship init zsh)"

# Manual Transient Logic
# This re-defines the 'accept-line' (Enter key) behavior
function alex-transient-prompt-accept-line() {
    export STARSHIP_TRANSIENT=1
    zle .reset-prompt
    unset STARSHIP_TRANSIENT
    zle .accept-line
}

zle -N accept-line alex-transient-prompt-accept-line
Then, in your starship.toml, you define what the "minimal" prompt looks like:

Ini, TOML
# ~/.config/starship.toml

[transient_prompt]
command_symbol = "❯ "
